Rather than us discussing someone who's upset about an article from over a year ago, let's look at some future stuff!

As a reminder to everyone, as of January we're instituting the week-in-advance submission deadline rather than the two-day deadline, so that I can better keep up with the influx of writers.
This also means that if we find big problems with the article (rules mistakes, controversial content, egregious failure to grasp the English language, Marchesa-Bolas fanfiction, that sort of thing) I may push it back to the author to fix those up before publishing, so there's more time to work things out and correct them.

This won't apply to Set Review articles, because we like the turnaround on those to be basically ASAP once the set is out.

Speaking of which, we should discuss the Set Review articles now that spoilers are arriving. Last time for GRN, we split the cards based on Guild, with two extra articles for noteworthy Guildless cards. I see no reason why this time should be different.

GUILDS (Distinguished by Watermark)
Orzhov - Dean has requested
Rakdos - Dana
Simic -
Azorius -
Gruul - Mason
Guildless Part 1 (White, Blue, Black) -
Guildless Part 2 (Red, Green, Artifacts, Lands) -

We may eventually come up with a more sophisticated method of selecting authors for set reviews, but for now, especially after the holidays, letting people chime in if they're available to do them is going to be most convenient.

For the love of all that is unholy, please refer to the Style Guide for the Set Review articles. I made an entire section at the end of it about how to write and format them. There have been some stinkers in the past, both in terms of formatting and content, and as mentioned at the beginning of this message, I'm gonna be stricter about quality. Our readers expect quality.

Cheers, all!
